WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:04.040 --> 00:00:11.040
VOICE
This July 4th, revisit the movie

00:00:11.260 --> 00:00:13.599
that made blowing up American
landmarks cool...

00:00:13.599 --> 00:00:17.869
VOICE (CONT'D)
...until 9/11... but now, 12 years

00:00:17.869 --> 00:00:19.900
later, it's apparently cool again?

00:00:19.900 --> 00:00:21.160
VOICE (CONT'D)
Independence Day.

00:00:21.160 --> 00:00:23.989
VOICE (CONT'D)
A film that answered whether we're

00:00:23.989 --> 00:00:27.489
alone in the universe, by stealing
from all the other films that

00:00:27.489 --> 00:00:30.160
answered whether we're alone in the
universe. Featuring...

00:00:30.160 --> 00:00:32.439
VOICE (CONT'D)
The premise from War of the Worlds

00:00:32.439 --> 00:00:33.899
VOICE (CONT'D)
The aliens from Alien

00:00:33.899 --> 00:00:35.130
VOICE (CONT'D)
The spaceships from V

00:00:35.130 --> 00:00:37.450
VOICE (CONT'D)
The Dogfights from Star Wars

00:00:37.450 --> 00:00:38.910
VOICE (CONT'D)
The statue of liberty from Planet

00:00:38.910 --> 00:00:39.710
of the Apes

00:00:39.710 --> 00:00:41.320
VOICE (CONT'D)
(And) the Jeff Goldblum from

00:00:41.320 --> 00:00:43.030
Jurassic Park

00:00:43.030 --> 00:00:47.780
VOICE (CONT'D)
To battle against an alien threat,

00:00:47.780 --> 00:00:50.900
humanity's last hope is this rag
tag group of survivors:

00:00:50.900 --> 00:00:53.690
VOICE (CONT'D)
Fighter pilot Steven Hiller, a

00:00:53.690 --> 00:00:57.030
Fresh Prince of the Air, who says
cool things, even when there's no

00:00:57.030 --> 00:01:01.090
one around to hear them.

00:01:09.490 --> 00:01:10.600
VOICE (CONT'D)
David Levinson. A Jeff Goldblum-like satellite engineer...

00:01:29.460 --> 00:01:32.140
VOICE (CONT'D)
And Thomas Whitmore: The best movie president ever...

00:01:32.140 --> 00:01:39.140
VOICE (CONT'D)
Who channels William Shatner.

00:01:44.390 --> 00:01:49.830
VOICE (CONT'D)
Prepare to stand up and cheer as

00:01:49.830 --> 00:01:52.500
they defeat an advanced alien race
with...

00:01:52.500 --> 00:01:54.979
VOICE (CONT'D)
A sheet.

00:01:54.979 --> 00:01:56.340
VOICE (CONT'D)
Morse-Code.

00:01:56.340 --> 00:02:00.000
VOICE (CONT'D)
Punching.

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:03.900
VOICE (CONT'D)
An Apple Powerbook 5300.

00:02:03.900 --> 00:02:06.840
VOICE (CONT'D)
And Cousin Eddie.

00:02:06.840 --> 00:02:12.930
VOICE (CONT'D)
Travel back to a time when summer

00:02:12.930 --> 00:02:19.930
